,"type":"text"},{"text":"2 VMs, each VM runs a Jenkins agent — doubling your Mac CI capacity.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Prerequisites","anchor":"Prerequisites","type":"heading","level":2},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Apple Silicon Mac with Spooktacular installed","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Jenkins controller (runs on any OS)","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"SSH connectivity between Jenkins controller and Mac host","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"A base VM with Xcode and the Jenkins agent installed","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"text":"Creating a Base Image","anchor":"Creating-a-Base-Image","type":"heading","level":2},{"syntax":"bash","type":"codeListing","code":["# Create the base VM","spook create jenkins-base --from-ipsw latest","","# Install Xcode and Jenkins agent in the base VM","# (Use SSH after the VM boots, or disk-inject provisioning)","spook start jenkins-base","spook ssh jenkins-base","","# Inside the VM:","# 1. Install Xcode from the App Store or xcode-select","# 2. Download the Jenkins agent .jar from your Jenkins controller","# 3. Create a LaunchAgent to start the agent on boot"]},{"text":"Provisioning Script","anchor":"Provisioning-Script","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Create a provisioning script that registers the VM as a Jenkins agent:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"bash","type":"codeListing","code":["#!\/bin\/bash","# jenkins-agent-setup.sh","","JENKINS_URL=\"https:\/\/jenkins.example.com\"","AGENT_NAME=\"$(hostname)\"","AGENT_SECRET=\"YOUR_AGENT_SECRET\"","","# Download the agent .jar","curl -sO \"$JENKINS_URL\/jnlpJars\/agent.jar\"","","# Start the agent","java -jar agent.jar \\","  -url \"$JENKINS_URL\" \\","  -secret \"$AGENT_SECRET\" \\","  -name \"$AGENT_NAME\" \\","  -workDir \"\/Users\/admin\/jenkins\""]},{"text":"Clone and Start Agents","anchor":"Clone-and-Start-Agents","type":"heading","level":2},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"bash","code":["# Clone the base image for each agent","spook clone jenkins-base jenkins-agent-01","spook clone jenkins-base jenkins-agent-02","","# Start with the provisioning script","spook start jenkins-agent-01 --headless \\","  --user-data .\/jenkins-agent-setup.sh --provision ssh","","spook start jenkins-agent-02 --headless \\","  --user-data .\/jenkins-agent-setup.sh --provision ssh"]},{"anchor":"Ephemeral-Agents","type":"heading","text":"Ephemeral Agents","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"For clean builds every time, use ephemeral mode. The VM is","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"destroyed after the agent disconnects:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"bash","code":["spook start jenkins-agent-01 --headless --ephemeral \\","  --user-data .\/jenkins-agent-setup.sh --provision ssh"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Combine with a cron job or Jenkins pipeline that re-clones"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and re-starts agents between builds."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Running as a Service","anchor":"Running-as-a-Service","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"For persistent agents that survive Mac reboots:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"bash","code":["sudo spook service install jenkins-agent-01","sudo spook service install jenkins-agent-02"]},{"anchor":"Kubernetes-Integration","type":"heading","text":"Kubernetes Integration","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If your Jenkins runs on Kubernetes, use the Spooktacular"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Kubernetes operator to manage agents declaratively:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"yaml","code":["apiVersion: spooktacular.app\/v1alpha1","kind: MacOSVM","metadata:","  name: 